<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" ><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.2.1">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><updated>2022-09-26T20:26:01+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/feed.xml</id><title type="html">Hermosawave Photography</title><subtitle>A series of daily landscape photographs by Daniel Sofer, 20 years running.</subtitle><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><entry><title type="html">River Dawn・川の夜明け</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220926/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="River Dawn・川の夜明け" /><published>2022-09-26T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-09-26T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/river-dawn</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220926/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
Row boats are lined up as the day begins. Mt. Hiei glows in the dawns’ early light.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
手漕ぎボートがずらりと並び、一日が始まる。比叡山は夜明けの光を浴びている。

&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Dawn" /><category term="Katsura River" /><category term="Boats" /><category term="Mountains" /><summary type="html">Row boats are lined up as the day begins. Mt. Hiei glows in the dawns’ early light.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_IMG_6047.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_IMG_6047.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Blue Morning・青い朝</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220925/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Blue Morning・青い朝" /><published>2022-09-25T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-09-25T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/blue-morning</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220925/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
The typhoon passed, the fog lifted, and blue sky appeared on Lake Ashi in Hakone. However, Mt. Fuji is still sleeping behind the clouds...
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
台風が過ぎ去り、霧が晴れ、箱根の芦ノ湖には青空が広がりました。富士山はまだ雲の向こうで眠っています...。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Japan" /><category term="Lakes" /><category term="Shrines" /><summary type="html">The typhoon passed, the fog lifted, and blue sky appeared on Lake Ashi in Hakone. However, Mt. Fuji is still sleeping behind the clouds...</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_IMG_6041.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_IMG_6041.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Lake Ashi・芦ノ湖</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220924/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Lake Ashi・芦ノ湖" /><published>2022-09-24T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-09-24T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/hakone</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220924/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
Boats and shrine on a cloudy day, on Lake Ashi in Hakone.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
曇りの日の箱根・芦ノ湖のボートと神社。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Japan" /><category term="Lakes" /><category term="Boats" /><category term="Shrines" /><summary type="html">Boats and shrine on a cloudy day, on Lake Ashi in Hakone.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02638.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02638.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Evening on the Yodogawa・淀川の夕焼</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220921/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Evening on the Yodogawa・淀川の夕焼" /><published>2022-09-21T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-09-21T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/yodogawa</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220921/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
Looking northwest over the Yodo River at the cities of Amagasaki and Toyonaka, across the river from Osaka, in this shot from the top of the Umeda Sky Building. 
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
During the Edo period (1603-1867), Osaka was home to so many bridges that it was known as ”Naniwa Happyaku Hachi Bashi” (Naniwa 808 bridges). However, there were not really 808 bridges; in fact, there were only about 200. But today Osaka lists 872 bridges in the city, of which four are shown here.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
梅田スカイビルの屋上から撮影した、淀川を挟んだ尼崎市と豊中市の風景です。
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
江戸時代、大阪は「浪華八百八橋」といわれるほど多くの橋が架けられました。
　808という数字がありますが、本当に808の橋があったわけではありません。実際には200ほど。しかし、現在では市内に872の橋があり、そのうちの4つがここに紹介する橋である。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Osaka" /><category term="Dusk" /><category term="Bridges" /><category term="Rivers" /><summary type="html">Looking northwest over the Yodo River at the cities of Amagasaki and Toyonaka, across the river from Osaka, in this shot from the top of the Umeda Sky Building. During the Edo period (1603-1867), Osaka was home to so many bridges that it was known as ”Naniwa Happyaku Hachi Bashi” (Naniwa 808 bridges). However, there were not really 808 bridges; in fact, there were only about 200. But today Osaka lists 872 bridges in the city, of which four are shown here.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02572.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02572.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Fushimi Castle・伏見城</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220917/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Fushimi Castle・伏見城" /><published>2022-09-17T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-09-17T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/fushimi-castle</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220917/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fushimi_Castle&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Fushimi Castle&lt;/a&gt;, a replica built in 1964, looking out over the mountains (and transmission lines) of southern Kyoto, in this photo taken from Kyoto Tower.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
  京都タワーから撮影した、京都南部の山並みを見下ろす&lt;a href=&quot;https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E4%BC%8F%E8%A6%8B%E5%9F%8E&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;伏見城&lt;/a&gt;。1964年に建てられたレプリカです。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Castles" /><summary type="html">Fushimi Castle, a replica built in 1964, looking out over the mountains (and transmission lines) of southern Kyoto, in this photo taken from Kyoto Tower.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02485.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02485.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Higanbana・彼岸花</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220916/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Higanbana・彼岸花" /><published>2022-09-16T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-09-16T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/higanbana</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220916/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
Red spider lilies (Higanbana) in a sea of green, at Daikaku-ji Temple.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
  緑色の海にヒガンバナ、大覚寺にて。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Flowers" /><category term="Daikaku-ji" /><summary type="html">Red spider lilies (Higanbana) in a sea of green, at Daikaku-ji Temple.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02447.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02447.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Arashiyama・嵐山</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220915/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Arashiyama・嵐山" /><published>2022-09-15T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-09-15T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/arashiyama</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220915/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
A sunny afternoon on the river.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
川沿い晴れたの午後。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Katsura River" /><category term="Boats" /><summary type="html">A sunny afternoon on the river.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_IMG_5991.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_IMG_5991.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Golden Rails・金色の線路</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220913/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Golden Rails・金色の線路" /><published>2022-09-13T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-09-13T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/golden-tracks</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220913/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
Setting sun lights up the tracks at Kyoto Station.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
京都駅の線路を照らす夕日。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Trains" /><summary type="html">Setting sun lights up the tracks at Kyoto Station.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02409.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02409.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">A Cool Breeze・鴨川の涼しい風</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220912/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="A Cool Breeze・鴨川の涼しい風" /><published>2022-09-12T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-09-12T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/kamogawa</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220912/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
After sunset, the cool breeze from the Kamogawa River provides a welcome respite from the hot day.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
日没後、鴨川からの涼しい風が暑い一日を癒してくれる感じです。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Dusk" /><category term="Kamo River" /><summary type="html">After sunset, the cool breeze from the Kamogawa River provides a welcome respite from the hot day.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02397.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02397.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Fog in the Mountains・山の霧</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220911/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Fog in the Mountains・山の霧" /><published>2022-09-11T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-09-11T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/mountain-fog</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220911/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
Looking northwest across the Katsura River at Mount Atago. Early morning fog often forms in the the canyons.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
桂川を挟んで北西にある愛宕山を望む。渓谷には早朝に霧が発生することが多い。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Dawn" /><category term="Katsura River" /><category term="Fog" /><summary type="html">Looking northwest across the Katsura River at Mount Atago. Early morning fog often forms in the the canyons.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02381.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2209_A7R02381.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry></feed>